gov.usgs.anss.edgemom

Class NoDBConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • gov.usgs.anss.edgethread.EdgeThread
        • gov.usgs.anss.edgemom.NoDBConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class NoDBConfig
extends EdgeThread
    This class computes files based on a key-value value files and the templates in the NoDB directory. All files have substitutions done for all of the key value pairs and the files are moved to the same positions they have in NoDB relative to the current directory - that is if there is a file NoDB/EW/import.setup the substituted file will be in ./EW/import.setup. Normally this would either be run manually during a normal setup, or it can be run as a Thread under EdgeMom so that changes in the key value file are propagated every 2 minutes.
    The routine checks the modified dates of the property and key files and if they have been changed then the files are check to see if they are the same as the cached copy of those files from the last full run. If either of the files is different, then the full substitution is performed. The check for modified dates can be skipped with the -nodate option which is used on systems that do not support the modified date on files. 
     switch    value        description
 -config  keyfile   Set the key-value file name to this instead of the default "config/edgemom.config"
 -prop    propfile  If another property file is needed to complete the conversion (def=edge.prop)
 -once              If present only run the conversion once and then exit
 -wait    secs      The number of seconds to wait between passes (def=120)
 -nodate            If present, the key and property files check for modified dates and the files are always read.
